      <processinfo id="aspace_67abf9216e44e37b47d522d58c7004ac">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_45f32e135fd43341b3a9279f49483ec0">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of correspondence, subject files, letters, lists, bulletins, a register, memorabilia, a 16mm film and financial materials documenting the Yale Art Gallery and art at Yale.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_8284dd2e04ff4abdb14e1318484cb2ba">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
